1002
01:08:29.807 --> 01:08:31.466
(stabs)

1003
01:08:31.508 --> 01:08:35.203
♪

1004
01:08:35.245 --> 01:08:38.173
(groaning)

1005
01:08:38.215 --> 01:08:44.547
♪

1006
01:08:44.589 --> 01:08:46.816
- (squelching)
- (grunting)


1007
01:08:46.858 --> 01:08:50.418
♪

1008
01:08:50.460 --> 01:08:52.220
- Oh, Jesus.
- Oh, my God.


1009
01:08:52.262 --> 01:08:58.460
♪

1010
01:08:58.502 --> 01:09:00.295
(squelching)

1011
01:09:00.337 --> 01:09:06.836
♪

1012
01:09:06.878 --> 01:09:08.738
- It's Anne-Marie.
- Don't touch it!


1013
01:09:08.780 --> 01:09:09.781
She's gone.

1014
01:09:10.380 --> 01:09:11.974
They never come back
the same.


1015
01:09:12.016 --> 01:09:16.712
♪

1016
01:09:16.754 --> 01:09:19.691
It's the kindest thing
we can do for her now, Saul.


1017
01:09:21.291 --> 01:09:22.885
I've known her
since she was a baby.


1018
01:09:22.927 --> 01:09:24.486
Saul.

1019
01:09:24.528 --> 01:09:26.421
♪

1020
01:09:26.463 --> 01:09:28.724
- (growling)
- Saul!


1021
01:09:28.766 --> 01:09:30.793
(screaming)

1022
01:09:30.835 --> 01:09:31.803
- Saul!
- Saul!


1023
01:09:32.003 --> 01:09:33.963
(screaming intensifies)

1024
01:09:34.005 --> 01:09:35.698
Oh, Jesus Christ!

1025
01:09:35.740 --> 01:09:36.832
Saul!

1026
01:09:36.874 --> 01:09:38.466
(screaming)

1027
01:09:38.508 --> 01:09:40.603
Saul, shoot her!

1028
01:09:40.645 --> 01:09:41.637
Do it now!

1029
01:09:41.679 --> 01:09:43.371
(gunshot)

1030
01:09:43.413 --> 01:09:45.675
(gasping)

1031
01:09:45.717 --> 01:09:48.753
♪

1032
01:09:49.554 --> 01:09:51.446
(breathing heavily)

1033
01:09:51.488 --> 01:09:57.485
♪

1034
01:09:57.527 --> 01:10:00.330
Is this a fate
that has befallen my son?


1035
01:10:01.566 --> 01:10:04.334
(thunder rumbling)

1036
01:10:06.604 --> 01:10:09.598
Isabelle must never know
about this, I beg you.


1037
01:10:09.640 --> 01:10:12.342
What else
doesn't she know about?


1038
01:10:15.312 --> 01:10:16.914
Do you dream much,
Seamus?


1039
01:10:17.782 --> 01:10:20.442
The land of Gévaudan
had been cursed.


1040
01:10:20.484 --> 01:10:23.045
At night, everyone had
the same dream.


1041
01:10:23.087 --> 01:10:24.287
Who is she?

1042
01:10:24.856 --> 01:10:26.048
What?

1043
01:10:26.090 --> 01:10:28.349
The woman buried
in the field.


1044
01:10:28.391 --> 01:10:30.052
Woman... I don't know
what you're talking about.


1045
01:10:30.094 --> 01:10:32.329
She cursed the land.

1046
01:10:33.463 --> 01:10:34.623
That's absurd.

1047
01:10:34.665 --> 01:10:36.859
Is what you just saw absurd?

1048
01:10:36.901 --> 01:10:38.527
The dreams, the beast.

1049
01:10:38.569 --> 01:10:40.930
You were cursed,
and it started with Edward.


1050
01:10:40.972 --> 01:10:43.999
Edward? Edward had
nothing to do with this.


1051
01:10:44.041 --> 01:10:46.635
He will kill
and keep on killing.


1052
01:10:46.677 --> 01:10:48.871
- Edward is innocent.
- Anyone who survives an attack


1053
01:10:48.913 --> 01:10:51.073
will change until the curse
has had its revenge.


1054
01:10:51.115 --> 01:10:53.809
Revenge? I am the one
seeking revenge


1055
01:10:53.851 --> 01:10:56.621
for what this thing
has done to my family!


1056
01:10:57.088 --> 01:11:00.057
(breathing heavily)

1057
01:11:00.658 --> 01:11:02.359
I started this,
so I will finish it.


1058
01:11:04.128 --> 01:11:06.931
I will hunt it myself and put
an end to it once and for all.


1059
01:11:08.833 --> 01:11:11.536
Now you burn
this thing...


1060
01:11:13.971 --> 01:11:15.840
...whatever it is.

1061
01:11:18.142 --> 01:11:20.645
(thunder rumbling)

1062
01:11:21.946 --> 01:11:23.572
Get the torch.

1063
01:11:23.614 --> 01:11:25.448
(door closing)

1064
01:11:27.819 --> 01:11:28.878
(cloth smacks)

1065
01:11:28.920 --> 01:11:31.689
(squawking)

1066
01:11:32.690 --> 01:11:34.625
(rain falling)

1067
01:11:45.803 --> 01:11:48.039
Please don't leave us,
Nana.


1068
01:11:48.940 --> 01:11:51.341
(sobbing)

1069
01:11:55.445 --> 01:11:57.615
Go on, Charlotte.

1070
01:12:06.858 --> 01:12:10.061
(sobbing)

1071
01:12:26.944 --> 01:12:29.572
- (door creaking closed)
- (sobbing)


1072
01:12:29.614 --> 01:12:31.749
(door locking)

1073
01:12:33.084 --> 01:12:35.410
(wood sliding)

1074
01:12:35.452 --> 01:12:36.821
Isabelle...

1075
01:12:38.789 --> 01:12:41.391
Who is the woman
buried in the field?


1076
01:12:49.834 --> 01:12:53.495
It's the only trophy
that's kept locked in a drawer


1077
01:12:53.537 --> 01:12:55.573
and not displayed
on the wall.


1078
01:12:58.075 --> 01:13:00.477
We must find
what was buried.


1079
01:13:02.813 --> 01:13:04.707
(dogs barking)

1080
01:13:04.749 --> 01:13:07.885
We've all dreamt of the silver
that has cursed this land.


1081
01:13:09.787 --> 01:13:13.157
On the body of Timmy, I found
a page torn from the Bible.


1082
01:13:14.959 --> 01:13:17.720
He knew something
about the silver,


1083
01:13:17.762 --> 01:13:19.997
as there was
a passage underlined.


1084
01:13:21.065 --> 01:13:23.826
"As silver is melted
in the furnace,


1085
01:13:23.868 --> 01:13:26.637
so will you be melted
in its midst;


1086
01:13:29.540 --> 01:13:31.033
and you shall know
that I, the Lord,


1087
01:13:31.075 --> 01:13:33.836
have poured out My fury
upon you."


1088
01:13:33.878 --> 01:13:36.138
(rumbling of hooves)

1089
01:13:36.180 --> 01:13:40.643
♪

1090
01:13:40.685 --> 01:13:44.922
Ezekiel 22:22.

1091
01:13:47.992 --> 01:13:49.193
Charlotte...

1092
01:13:50.828 --> 01:13:52.663
